TopicTitle: Folding Plane .craft files **FIXED for realz!** Updated 6/2/2012

Articles.Content:
First of you have to have the [Damned Robotics Version 1.1](http://kerbalspaceprogram.com/forum/index.php?topic=10662.0) and [Anatid Robotics / MuMech - MechJeb - Autopilot - v1.8.4](http://kerbalspaceprogram.com/forum/index.php?topic=8021.0)

Apparently I used a couple of parts from [C7 Aerospace Division - Part 3](http://kerbalspaceprogram.com/forum/index.php?topic=1172.0) and the [C7 Flight Pack](http://www.kspyard.com/mods/packages/C7+Flight+Pack+Version+2.15/#.T8tJtMVCdkF) too. Sorry for not linking this needed stuff earlier.

Floodlights are here: [Omega Aerospace](http://kerbalspaceprogram.com/forum/index.php?topic=10128.0)

NP\*stuff\* parts from: [NovaPunch Remix Pack](http://kerbalspaceprogram.com/forum/index.php?topic=4180.0)

\*\*UPDATED\*\* Next you need a bunch of hinges that I tweaked based off of Damnyoujapan\'s and r4m0n\'s work in the above add-on, extra thanks to them for making these awesome toys or us to play with! The modified hinges are the attachment 'ModifiedDRstuff.zip' . Just extract them into your parts folder.

Ultra RCS attachment is a blatant cheat part that I use for testing and balancing, but I may have left it on a craft or 2.

All of these start unfolded for the most part. Use \'0\' and \'9\' to fold or unfold, and make sure to unfold them all the way before you start.
